               is a first step in deciphering the mechanisms of its genesis and
               the fCNA's subsequent biological consequences. We introduce a
               computational method, AmpliconReconstructor (AR), for
               integrating optical mapping (OM) of long DNA fragments (>150 kb)
               with next-generation sequencing (NGS) to resolve fCNAs at
               single-nucleotide resolution. AR uses an NGS-derived breakpoint
